						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in the Brahmadēva temple.</p>						

						<p>[Dēvarāya II], 1431 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated the cyclic year Virōdhi, Pushya śu. 15, the Śaka year being lost. The name of the king, who might be Dēvarāya II, is not fully preserved and the cyclic year may be a mistake for Virōdhikṛit. In that case the date of the inscription would be 1431 A.D., December 19.</p>						

						<p>It records the renovation of the temple of Traimūrti at Saiviḍi in Bādāvi-sīme by Chavuḍaya-nāyaka, son of Tipaṇa-nāyaka of Bāgilavāḍa.</p>						

						</summary>
